Email Notification Plugin in Jenkins

Email notification in Jenkins
It allows you to receive emails about the build status, test results, or other important events related to your Jenkins jobs.
Install the Email Notification Plugin:
Go to "Manage Jenkins" > "Manage Plugins."
In the "Available" tab, search for "Email Notification Plugin" and install it.
Generation of App password
To generate the app password you need to go to the gmail account which you want to use to send mail.
Profile >> Manage google account >> security >> Enable 2 factor notification >> Generate App password.
Save the generated password.
Configure the Email Server in Jenkins:
Go to "Manage Jenkins" > "Configure System."
Scroll down to the "Email Notification" section.
Configure your SMTP server settings, including the SMTP server name, SMTP port, username (your email) and password(generated above).
Test the Configuration.
Configure the Job to Send Email Notifications:
Open the Jenkins job for which you want to configure email notifications.
Click on "Configure" to edit the job settings.
Scroll down to the "Post-build Actions" section
